latestIgtvVideos.title: What to wear, when you’ve "nothing to wear" 🤍
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here are a few looks I've put together with the most basic pieces of clothing I could get my hands on!

Look 1
•Graphic tee: Marks and Spencer 
Pair or colour block your graphic tee w literally any ethinic bottoms.
Surprise them with this perfect indo-western look!

Look 2
•Grey Sweatshirt:  Thrifted
•Grey Joggers: Puma

The most comfy yet super groovy. Pair it w yo favourite kicks! •Denim jacket: United Colours of Benetton
Go ahead, add a bit of pixie dust, to your old monochromatic look w a  denim jacket. 
Keep it casual yet chic!

Look 3
•Black Jeans: H&M •Top: Fabindia •Head band: An exhibition

Go ahead, pair the classic pair of black jeans with the most vibrant colours. 
Can never go wrong!

Look 4
•Dad's shirt: Levi's •Pants: Fabindia

Certainly had to dig through his closet, pick yo fav shirt, pair it w a pair of pants ORRR
JOGGERS! •Blue Joggers: Puma

Look 5
•Basic black/white tee: H&M •Salwar: Customised •Dupatta: Fabindia
 I robbed my mom's wardrobe for this look.  Went ahead w the basic black tee, paired it w salwar and dupatta of the same colour palette & Voila!

Hope, this helps!
xx
